				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That is not true, you can allow *ONE of TWO* CHR RAM to be written outside of Vblank by the CPU as long as it's disconnected from the PPU bus. All it takes is an address bus multiplexer and bi-directional tri-states or multiplexers on the data lines + control logic. Since WRAM is entirely connected to the FPGA in PowerPak, it is possible to use it for any general purpose storage.</div>

